[SN]TITLE[SN]
Financial stocks lead FTSE 100 higher

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Close): London's leading shares rose for a third straight day on Wednesday, as financial stocks led the gainers.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stockbroker Hargreaves Lansdown was the biggest winner, rising 4%, ahead of financial firm Old Mutual, which gained 3%.
Other big winners included pensions provider Standard Life and wealth manager St James's Place.
The benchmark FTSE 100 index closed on 6,261.19, which was an increase of 0.56% or 34.64 points.
On the currency markets, the pound rose 0.12% against the dollar to $1.4670, but edged lower against the euro to â‚¬1.3005.
Hospitality group Whitbread, which had led the list of gainers at the start of trading, later fell back to stand 0.9% lower on the day. A positive trading update had boosted it by 1.8% on Tuesday.
